---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Morristown Eats"
  description="Who runs this, why it exists, and how we decide what to write about. No ads, no pay-to-play, no chain-first coverage."
>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width: 680px; margin: 0 auto;">

        <div class="breadcrumb" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">
          <a href="/">Home</a>
          <span class="breadcrumb-sep">→</span>
          <span class="breadcrumb-current">About</span>
        </div>

        <h1 style="margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">About Morristown Eats</h1>

        <p style="font-size: var(--text-lg); line-height: var(--leading-loose); color: var(--color-ink-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-8);">
          Morristown has a real food scene. It doesn't have a real food guide. This is an attempt to fix that.
        </p>

        <hr class="divider" />

        <h2 style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-5);">Who runs this</h2>
        <p style="line-height: var(--leading-loose); margin-bottom: var(--space-5);">
          Morristown Eats is a one-person project. I'm a Morristown resident who eats out constantly,
          knows this town's restaurant scene, and got tired of the available options — Yelp noise,
          Tripadvisor nonsense, generic food blogs that haven't updated since 2019, and a local Instagram
          account that runs spectacle events and charges restaurants for coverage.
        </p>
        <p style="line-height: var(--leading-loose); margin-bottom: var(--space-8);">
          I built this because the town deserves something better. Something specific, honest,
          and written by someone who actually lives here.
        </p>

        <hr class="divider" />

        <h2 id="methodology" style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-5);">Our methodology</h2>

        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">We visit first. We write second.</h3>
        <p style="line-height: var(--leading-loose); margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">
          No restaurant profile goes live with editorial content until we've visited in person.
          Some profiles are published as verified fact shells — address, hours, cuisine — while
          the visit is pending. These are clearly marked. The editorial take, dish recommendations,
          and ratings are only published after eating there.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">We pay for our own meals.</h3>
        <p style="line-height: var(--leading-loose); margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">
          Always. No exceptions. We don't accept free meals, complimentary tastings, press events,
          or any form of hosted visit. If a restaurant knows we're coming, that's a conflict.
          We go as anonymous customers.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">No pay-to-play. Ever.</h3>
        <p style="line-height: var(--leading-loose); margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">
          No restaurant pays for coverage, featured placement, or profile publication.
          Advertising does not exist on this platform. There is no premium listing tier.
          Coverage is earned by being worth covering, nothing else.
          This rule is the entire competitive moat of this project and it will never change.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">Independent restaurants first.</h3>
        <p style="line-height: var(--leading-loose); margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">
          The platform prioritizes independently owned and locally owned restaurants.
          Regional chains with significant local roots can be listed and reviewed but are
          clearly disclosed and are not eligible for our top awards tier.
          National chains are not listed.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">How we rate restaurants</h3>
        <p style="line-height: var(--leading-loose); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
          We use four dimensions, rated on a 1–10 editorial scale:
        </p>
        <ul style="list-style: none; margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">
          {[
            { label: 'Consistency', desc: 'Reliable quality across multiple visits — not just good on a lucky night.' },
            { label: 'Distinctiveness', desc: 'Does something you can\'t easily get elsewhere in Morristown.' },
            { label: 'Execution', desc: 'Technical skill in the kitchen — the food is made well.' },
            { label: 'Local Relevance', desc: 'How central this restaurant is to Morristown\'s dining identity.' },
          ].map(r => (
            <li style="padding: var(--space-4) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); display: grid; grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr; gap: var(--space-4);">
              <span style="font-size: var(--text-sm); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide); text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-ink);">{r.label}</span>
              <span style="color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: var(--leading-normal);">{r.desc}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
        <p style="line-height: var(--leading-loose); margin-bottom: var(--space-8);">
          There is no overall score. Ratings are editorial assessments, not averages of crowdsourced reviews.
          A restaurant is not penalized for being a great pizza counter rather than a great date-night table —
          it's rated on whether it does its thing well.
        </p>

        <hr class="divider" />

        <h2 style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-5);">What this is not</h2>
        <p style="line-height: var(--leading-loose); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
          Morristown Eats is not Yelp, Tripadvisor, or a comments platform.
          There are no public reviews. There are no star ratings from strangers.
          There is no way for anyone — restauranteur, competitor, or disgruntled customer — to
          post negative content about a business.
        </p>
        <p style="line-height: var(--leading-loose); margin-bottom: var(--space-8);">
          This is an editorial project. One voice, one standard, one clear methodology.
          If something is wrong, you can reach us directly.
        </p>

        <hr class="divider" />

        <h2 style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-5);">Get in touch</h2>
        <p style="line-height: var(--leading-loose); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
          Have a restaurant we should know about? Found an error? Want to talk?
          We're on Substack. Reach us through the newsletter.
        </p>
        <a href="https://morristowneats.substack.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-dark">
          Morristown Eats on Substack
        </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
